.TH "nvmf_context_set_device" 9 "nvmf_context_set_device" "March 2026" "libnvme API manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nvmf_context_set_device \- Set device for context
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nvmf_context_set_device
.BI "(struct nvmf_context *fctx "  ","
.BI "const char *device "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fctx" 12
Fabrics context
.IP "device" 12
Device path or identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets the device to be used by the context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or a negative error code on failure.
